Feature extraction scripts used for the experiments performed for the 
Bachelor's thesis entitled 
"Prototype-based Relevance Learning for Genre Classification". 

(c) 2007 Jan A. Gasthaus

FILES
=====
  * biberextractor.py
    
    Script to extract the features described in Appendix II of 
    "Variation across speech and writing" by D. Biber [1981].

  * posextractor.py
    
    Script to extract POS uni-, bi-, and trigram frequencies.

  * Several supplementary files on which these extractors are based, 
    amounting to a framework for extracting linguistic features from
    tab-separated, one-token-per-line corpus files.

Running the script without parameters will give a help message, but have a 
look at the source code for further information
.

